# Cursor Rules — sqlserver_mcp

## Project
.NET 8 MCP Server (based on Microsoft's MssqlMcp from SQL-AI-samples) bridging AI IDEs with SQL Server stockdata_db.

## Stack
- .NET 8, C#, Microsoft.Data.SqlClient, MCP C# SDK
- SQL Server (localhost\MSSQLSERVER01, stockdata_db, Windows Auth)
- stdio transport (not HTTP)
- CONNECTION_STRING environment variable for database connectivity

## Architecture
- `SQL-AI-samples/MssqlMcp/dotnet/MssqlMcp/` — Main project directory
- `Program.cs` — Entry point: `AddMcpServer()`, `WithStdioServerTransport()`, `WithToolsFromAssembly()`
- `SqlConnectionFactory.cs` — Reads CONNECTION_STRING env var, creates SqlConnection
- `Tools/Tools.cs` — Partial class with `ISqlConnectionFactory` DI
- `Tools/ListTables.cs` — Lists tables from INFORMATION_SCHEMA (read-only)
- `Tools/DescribeTable.cs` — Get schema/columns/types (read-only)
- `Tools/ReadData.cs` — Execute SQL queries (read-only)
- `Tools/CreateTable.cs` — Create new tables
- `Tools/DropTable.cs` — Drop tables (destructive!)
- `Tools/InsertData.cs` — Insert rows
- `Tools/UpdateData.cs` — Update rows
- All tools use `[McpServerTool]` attribute discovery

## SQL Scripts
- `trading_system_setup.sql` — Stored procs (sp_get_daily_trading_signals, sp_check_trading_alerts)
- `daily_trading_workflow.sql` — Morning pre-market workflow

## Configuration
```json
"MSSQL MCP": {
    "type": "stdio",
    "command": "C:\\Users\\sreea\\OneDrive\\Desktop\\sqlserver_mcp\\SQL-AI-samples\\MssqlMcp\\dotnet\\MssqlMcp\\bin\\Debug\\net8.0\\MssqlMcp.exe",
    "env": {
        "CONNECTION_STRING": "Server=localhost\\MSSQLSERVER01;Database=stockdata_db;Trusted_Connection=True;TrustServerCertificate=True"
    }
}
```

## Database Access
29+ tables, 40+ views in stockdata_db covering:
- Market data (NASDAQ/NSE/Forex OHLCV)
- ML predictions (3 pipelines)
- Technical indicators (RSI, MACD, BB, etc.)
- Strategy signals and tracking
- Portfolio and alerts

## Ecosystem
Infrastructure layer for 7-repo trading platform. Does not train models, run agents, or generate reports. Enables AI-assisted database exploration during development.
